        "header": "2SpatialWorldBenchmark",
        "images": [
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2606.09669/2606.09669v1/x1.png",
                "caption": "Figure 1:SpatialWorld is a scalable, general-purpose evaluation framework for multimodal agents, supporting end-to-end task solving and structured plan generation. It unifies diverse 3D backends under a standardized observation-action interface, enabling rigorous assessment of interactive spatial reasoning via reproducible benchmarks and automated efficiency metrics.",
                "position": 279
            },
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2606.09669/2606.09669v1/x2.png",
                "caption": "Figure 2:Data construction pipeline of SpatialWorld.We first collect a series of environments, have annotators learn tutorials and write instructions, define success conditions, and then calibrate the data through automated execution validation in virtual environments and human cross-validation.",
                "position": 302
            },
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2606.09669/2606.09669v1/x3.png",
                "caption": "Figure 3:The Observation and Action Interfaces.(a) Flexible environment initialization via direct state loading or action-list execution. (b) A unified interface providing standardized egocentric RGB observations. (c) A structured, unified action space𝒜\\mathcal{A}. (d) Action-to-code mapping that translates unified actions into environment-specific commands, enabling cross-simulator deployment.",
                "position": 500
            },
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2606.09669/2606.09669v1/x4.png",
                "caption": "Table 2:Scenario distribution.Task distribution across environments and scenario categories. “Social” denotes Social Collaboration; “Entertain.” denotes Entertainment.",
                "position": 537
            },
            {
